HP_Ice_Evolve is a MATLAB function that  simulates the thermal evolution of an ice sheet

Inputs:
T_n - a vertical temperature profile (K)
k   - a vertical thermal conductivity profile (W/m*K)
rho - a vertical density profile (kg/m^3)
c   - a vertical specific heat profile (J/kg*K)
dt  - a time step (s)
dz  - vertical spatial resolution (m)
T_surf - surface temperature (K)
Base_flux - basal heat flux (W/m^2)

Output:
Vertical temperature profile after timestep dt

Thus, to call the function type: Temp=HP_Ice_Evolve(T_n,k,rho,c,dt,dz,T_surf,Base_flux)

'Temp' will be the new temperature profile.
